{t: Northwest Passage}
{st: Stan Rogers  1981}

Chorus:
Ah, for [G]  just one [D] time I would [C] take the Northwest [Em] Passage
To [C] find the hand of [G]  Franklin reaching [Am] for the Beaufort [C] Sea;
Tracing [G]  one warm [D]  line through a [C] land so wide and [Em] savage
And [C] make a Northwest [G] Passage [D] to the [G] sea.

Verse 1:
[C] Westward from the [G] Davis Strait  ’tis there ’twas [D] said to lie
The [C]  sea route to the [G] Orient for which so [C] many died;
[C] Seeking gold and [Em] glory, leaving [G] weathered, broken [C] bones,
And a [C] long-forgotten [G] lonely [Em] cairn of stones.   

