Verse 2:
Three [C] centuries there [G] after, I take passage [D] overland.
In the [C]  footsteps of brave [G] Kelso, where his “sea of [C] flowers” began.
Watching [C] cities rise [Em] before me, then [G] behind me sink [C] again,
This [C] tardiest ex [G] plorer, driving [D] hard across the [C] plain.    

