Verse 3:
And [C] through the night, be [G] hind the wheel, the mileage [D] clicking west
I [C]  think upon Mac [G] kenzie, David Thompson [C] and the rest,
Who [C] cracked the mountain [Em] ramparts and did [G] show a path for [C] me
To [C] race the roaring [G] Fraser [Em]  to the sea.    

 

