Verse 4:
How [C] then am I so [G] different from the first men [D] through this way?
Like [C]  them, I left a [G] settled life, I threw it [C]  all away.
To [C] seek a Northwest [Em] Passage at the [G] call of many [C]  men,
To [C]  find there but the [G] road back [Em] home again.     

